-98872665.text: "In vitro studies showed that treatment of triple negative breast cancer (TNBC) MDA-MB-231 cells with Se-PFPs (1) inhibited cell growth dose-dependently by arresting cells at G2 phase via inhibiting CDC25C-CyclinB1 and CDC2 pathway; (2) caused apoptosis associated with increased p53, Bax, Puma and Noxa, decreased Bcl2, increased Bax and Bcl2 ratio and increased activities of caspases 3/9, suggesting its effect on p53 mediated cytochrome c-caspase pathway."
